  "productThoughts": [
    {"id":"THOUGHT-001","status":"accepted","text":"Identity must follow semantic code movement; line numbers and hashes alone are insufficient."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-002","status":"accepted","text":"VS Code and Tauri must share a domain contract and fixtures, not duplicate behavior."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-003","status":"accepted","text":"Ambiguous transitions must preserve recoverable data and expose orphan/re-anchor state."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-004","status":"accepted","text":"Bulk workflows, keyboard operation, conflict safety and reliable movement come before more AI surface."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-005","status":"accepted","text":"Drag-and-drop needs visible feedback and an accessible non-drag alternative."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-006","status":"investigate","text":"AST symbol identity plus block fingerprint and Git diff mapping may outperform line-context anchors."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-007","status":"investigate","text":"A shared local operation ledger could reconcile concurrent extension/desktop writes without a server."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-008","status":"investigate","text":"Retire the legacy manager after porting its clipboard heuristics; two lifecycle engines are a regression risk."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-009","status":"accepted","text":"Tracking diagnostics must expose hashes and decisions without copying proprietary source text into reports."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-010","status":"accepted","text":"Use Microsoft VS Code native surfaces for selection, confirmation, theme, accessibility and commands; keep the webview focused on dense cross-file workflows."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-011","status":"accepted","text":"Ship focused patch releases at verified milestones instead of accumulating UI, tracking and workflow risk into one large release."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-012","status":"accepted","text":"A stable VS Code editor decoration is visual only; direct manipulation must use clickable Inlay Hint/CodeLens/Comments commands or originate a drag from TreeView."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-013","status":"accepted","text":"Context menus should reveal capability progressively through named groups instead of one flat list of unrelated commands."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-014","status":"accepted","text":"DocumentPasteEditProvider metadata is the strongest stable SDK path to make copy/paste tracking deterministic without modifying source text."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-015","status":"accepted","text":"No Tauri or MCP writer may replace the shared envelope without checking the revision it originally read."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-016","status":"investigate","text":"Problems, Testing and Timeline projections should be opt-in and actionable so annotations do not become noise in native developer surfaces."}
    ,{"id":"THOUGHT-017","status":"accepted","text":"Continuous improvement is an ongoing roadmap loop: audit every existing capability, document it, fix regressions, research new value and publish each stable increment instead of postponing stability for an unbounded release."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-018","status":"accepted","text":"Document structure templates and output renderers must remain separate layers over one normalized annotation graph."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-019","status":"accepted","text":"OpenAPI routes are security-relevant structured data and must never be inferred from untrusted prose or tags."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-020","status":"accepted","text":"Generated documentation needs a manifest and transaction boundary so stale cleanup is precise and failed runs are reversible."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-021","status":"accepted","text":"A first-time user must be able to discover every workflow through native menus and empty-view guidance; the Command Palette and shortcuts are accelerators, not prerequisites."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-022","status":"accepted","text":"A visible public command must mutate or inspect the canonical active store, validate its target and explain missing prerequisites instead of delegating to an empty compatibility path or returning silently."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-023","status":"accepted","text":"Credential management must make storage visibility explicit, support reversible add/update/remove and clear every recognized legacy location when the user removes a provider key."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-024","status":"accepted","text":"External mutations require explicit confirmation and platform authentication; if the remote operation succeeds but local trace persistence fails, report the split outcome and preserve the remote URL to prevent duplicate retries."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-025","status":"accepted","text":"Source-comment interoperability must be bidirectional, language-aware, previewable, selectable, explicitly confirmed and reversible; stable identity markers must prevent repeated conversions from duplicating content."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-026","status":"accepted","text":"Atomic single-process persistence prevents truncation but does not solve concurrent writers; revision preconditions and shared ownership remain a separate required safety layer."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-027","status":"accepted","text":"A content fingerprint is a safer self-write signal than a timing window because only the exact bytes just committed may be ignored; a nearby external edit must still be processed."},
    {"id":"THOUGHT-028","status":"accepted","text":"Performance work on a security-sensitive writer must retain confinement, real-parent validation, integrity fingerprints and recoverability at every transaction phase; concurrency is bounded inside those invariants rather than bypassing them."}
  ]
};
